articles.description: Members of the Michigan State faculty voted 61-4 to express no confidence in the eight-member governing body at the university. Meanwhile, the institution's interim president wrote to the campus community about cooperation with ongoing investigations.
articles.headline: Michigan State faculty delivers no-confidence vote on board of trustees

images.caption: The Michigan State faculty's vote against the board of trustees came largely in response to the board's decision to name John Engler the school's interim president.
images.name: John Engler [600x400] - Copy (2)

images.caption: Michigan State students, including one who jumped onto and sat on the middle of a table, interrupt an MSU board of trustees meeting to protest the school's selection of John Engler as the interim president.
images.name: MSU students vent frustration over interim president selection

videos.description: After a few long passes, Kevin Knox finally finds Quade Green who knocks in a 3-pointer from the top of the key.
videos.headline: Kentucky's great ball movement leads to triple

videos.description: James Daniel III sends a perfect bounce pass to Kyle Alexander who throws down a one-handed jam in the first half.
videos.headline: Tennessee's Daniel drops dime to Alexander for slam

videos.description: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander spins inside and passes to Jarred Vanderbilt who punishes the rim with a two-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Alexander feeds Vanderbilt for the flush

videos.description: Nick Richards swats away Grant Williams' shot attempt then Quade Green gets it and speeds down the court to score a wide-open basket.
videos.headline: Richards' block leads to bucket for Kentucky

videos.description: Shai Gilgeous-Alexanders lobs a pass up to Nick Richards who finishes at the rim with a two-handed slam at the end of the first half.
videos.headline: Richards rises up for alley-oop jam

videos.description: Tennessee head coach Rick Barnes hopes his team can perfect their defensive play and capitalize on getting the ball in the second half against No. 24 Kentucky
videos.headline: Coach Barnes expects less turnovers in second half

videos.description: Kevin Knox gets inside to receive the inbounds lob pass from Shai Gilgeous-Alexander then Knox rises up for a massive slam dunk and gets fouled.
videos.headline: Wildcats create unbelievable 3-point play

videos.description: Grant Williams bounces a pass to Admiral Schofield who throws down a one-handed slam with authority.
videos.headline: Williams finds Schofield for the hammer

videos.description: Kevin Knox steals the ball from Lamonte Turner then zips down the court for a layup and gets fouled for a chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Knox races for and-1

videos.description: With less than seven seconds left the in the game, Jordan Bowden intercepts the ball and dishes it to Admiral Schofield on the other side of the court and he scores a two-handed dunk to give Tennessee a 3-point lead against Kentucky.
videos.headline: Great Tennessee defense leads to clutch bucket

videos.description: Lamonte Turner credits coach Rick Barnes for not calling a timeout when they were down by 2 and instead trusting him to score when it mattered most.
videos.headline: Turner on his crucial 3 for Tennessee

videos.description: Lamonte Turner looks like he wants to pass the ball but instead he knocks down a 3-pointer from the top of the key to put the Volunteers back in front late in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Turner drills triple for Tennessee lead

videos.description: The Vols complete a season sweep of the Wildcats after winning 61-59 at Rupp Arena.
videos.headline: No. 15 Tennessee knocks off No. 24 Kentucky

tracking.trackingName: SEC_NCB Highlight (Tennessee knocks off UK) 180206 ESHEET

videos.description: No. 15 Tennessee hits clutch shots down the stretch to sweep the season series against No. 24 Kentucky.
videos.headline: Tennessee hangs on to defeat Kentucky
